Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil for cooking{3%tsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @pineapple rings{1} from the tin, reserving the juice.
Chop the pineapple into 1cm chunks.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the pineapple, spring onion, half the
@chipotle paste{20%g}, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, a squeeze of lime juice,
and some salt and pepper. Set your pineapple salsa aside.

Drain the @firm tofu{280%g} and cut into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cornflour{20%g}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and
@salt{1/4%tsp}. Toss the tofu in the cornflour until completely coated.

Heat the oil for cooking in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently
to ensure it doesn't burn.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the remaining chipotle and
@soured cream{75%g}.

Once the tofu is crispy, transfer it to a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and put on medium-high heat. Add the
reserved pineapple juice and simmer until reduced by half, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Return the fried tofu to the pan and toss to coat until glazed.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a baking tray and into the
oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, lay the tortillas on your plates and spread each with
a spoonful of the chipotle soured cream.

Load up each taco with the glazed tofu and pineapple salsa - as much as you'd
like.

Serve the chips and any remaining lime wedges alongside.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!

> Our Glazed Tofu Tacos and Chips are a delicious veggie option that make it
> easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!